    <SUBJECT>Amendments to Exchange Act Rule 10b-5</SUBJECT>
    <AGY>
      <HD SOURCE="HED">AGENCY:</HD>
      <P>Securities and Exchange Commission.</P>
    </AGY>
    <ACT>
      <HD SOURCE="HED">ACTION:</HD>
      <P>Final rule.</P>
    </ACT>
    <SUM>
      <HD SOURCE="HED">SUMMARY:</HD>
      <P>The Commission is adopting amendments to Rule 10b-5 under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934.</P>
    </SUM>
    <DATES>
      <HD SOURCE="HED">DATES:</HD>
      <P><E T="03">Effective date:</E> March 30, 2026.</P>
    </DATES>
  </PREAMB>
  <SUPLINF>
    <HD SOURCE="HED">SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION:</HD>
    <HD SOURCE="HD1">I. Background</HD>
    <P>The Securities Exchange Act of 1934 governs the trading of securities.</P>
    <P>Section 10(b) of the Exchange Act makes it unlawful to use <I>any manipulative or deceptive device</I>.</P>
    <HD SOURCE="HD1">II. Discussion</HD>
    <P>The Commission has determined that these amendments are necessary.</P>
  </SUPLINF>
